text.section:
Each board of library trustees shall establish policies for:
Staff classification;
Salaries;
Work conditions;
Suspension with pay;
Grievance procedures;
Benefits, including vacation and sick leave;
Hours of work; and
Any other personnel procedures and practices necessary for the efficient operation of the library.

section.section:
The director or the director's designee may suspend a library employee without pay for a specified period up to 10 working days, for the following reasons:
Misconduct in office;
Insubordination;
Incompetency; or
Willful neglect of duty.

On written recommendation of the library director, each board of library trustees may dismiss any library employee under its jurisdiction for any of the following reasons:
Misconduct in office;
Insubordination;
Incompetency; or
Willful neglect of duty.

text.section:
The director of each library shall:
Act as the general executive officer of the library and be responsible for the management of its operations in accordance with policies approved by the board of library trustees;
Prepare the annual budget of the library, and present it to the board for approval;
Nominate for appointment all library employees in the county library system; and
Establish reasonable rules and adopt regulations for the use of the library system subject to approval by the board of library trustees.
